Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
snapFPlan(25.10)                                              snapFPlan(25.10)

Name
       snapFPlan - Snaps floorplan objects to the grid

Syntax
       snapFPlan

       [-help]

       {{-all} | {-selected} |

       {[-guide][-block][-stdCell][-ioPad][-areaIo][-ptnCore][-pin-
       Guide][-routeBlk][-placeBlk][-macroPin][-pin][-pinBlk]}}

       Snaps floorplan objects to the grid. You can use this command after im-
       porting the design.

       Note:  Innovus  honors the FinFET grid and automatically checks for the
       FinFET definition. If it detects a FinFET definition, it  enables  sup-
       port  and  sets the placement grid as FinFET grid by default. Since the
       height of all placeable objects must be a multiple of FinFET  grid  and
       the  origin  of  these  objects must be snapped to the FinFET grid. The
       snapFPlan command is used to snap blocks, I/O pads, standard  cells  to
       the  FinFET  grid.  It honors user specified snapping rule for x direc-
       tion. For y direction, it honors the FinFET grid (when the FinFET  grid
       is horizontal in regular horizontal row design).

Parameters
       -all   Specifies the snapping of all supported object types.

              Data_type: bool, required

       -areaIo
              Specifies the snapping of I/O cells.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -block Specifies the snapping of floorplan blocks.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -guide Specifies the snapping of floorplan guides, regions, and fences.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each snapFPlan parameter.  For  a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

                man snapFPlan

       -ioPad Specifies the snapping of I/O pads.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -macroPin
              Specifies the snapping of macro pins to the correct color track.

              Note: The snapFPlan command only snaps signal pins and places  a
              macro  with macro pins on color track. Innovus snaps the port on
              the lowest metal layer which is close to  macro  origin  to  the
              color track.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pin   Specifies the snapping of pins.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pinBlk
              Specifies the snapping of pin blockages.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pinGuide
              Specifies the snapping of pin guides.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -placeBlk
              Specifies the snapping of placement blockages.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -ptnCore
              Specifies the snapping of the partition core.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -routeBlk
              Specifies the snapping of routing blockages.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -selected
              Specifies  the  snapping  of all supported object types that are
              selected in the design display area.

              Data_type: bool, required

       -stdCell
              Specifies the snapping of standard cells.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Related Information
              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

